[{"data":1,"prerenderedAt":128},["ShallowReactive",2],{"header-locale:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F29\u002Fnodejs-mysterious-double-request\u002F":3,"page:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F29\u002Fnodejs-mysterious-double-request\u002F":4,"alt:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F29\u002Fnodejs-mysterious-double-request\u002F":3,"prev-next:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F29\u002Fnodejs-mysterious-double-request\u002F":103,"related:\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F29\u002Fnodejs-mysterious-double-request\u002F":112},"\u002Fnodejs\u002F20190429\u002F1130866276\u002F",{"id":5,"title":6,"abbrlink":7,"altUrl":3,"body":8,"category":85,"date":86,"description":87,"extension":88,"lang":89,"meta":90,"navigation":91,"path":92,"readingMinutes":93,"seo":94,"standalone":95,"stem":96,"tags":97,"tldr":100,"updated":100,"url":101,"__hash__":102},"content\u002Fen\u002FNodejs\u002Fnodejs-mysterious-double-request.md","Node.js's Mysterious Double Request","8627611036",{"type":9,"value":10,"toc":77},"minimark",[11,16,20,24,31,34,38,41,46,54,59,65,70,74],[12,13,15],"h2",{"id":14},"intro","Intro",[17,18,19],"p",{},"I've been studying Node.js + Firebase lately so haven't had much time to write. But while practicing Node.js I hit a really silly problem that stuck me for three days, so here's a note.",[12,21,23],{"id":22},"the-problem","The problem",[17,25,26],{},[27,28],"img",{"alt":29,"src":30},"Image","https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002F66AhQGE.png",[17,32,33],{},"Using Node.js, when requesting the auth page, for some reason the Request fires twice. That problem causes the connect-flash package to stop working.",[12,35,37],{"id":36},"the-fix","The fix",[17,39,40],{},"Later I asked someone for help, and they pointed me to the DevTools Network tab to check the loaded files. When I looked, I found these two...",[17,42,43],{},[27,44],{"alt":29,"src":45},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FQtTzTae.png",[17,47,48,49,53],{},"After seeing the request I immediately checked the HTML and realized I'd stuffed in a broken ",[50,51,52],"code",{},"\u003Cimg>",".",[17,55,56],{},[27,57],{"alt":29,"src":58},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FYXme4KQ.png",[17,60,61,62,64],{},"Delete the broken ",[50,63,52],{}," or give it a valid image path, and it works fine.",[17,66,67],{},[27,68],{"alt":29,"src":69},"https:\u002F\u002Fi.imgur.com\u002FpnSbs8B.png",[12,71,73],{"id":72},"wrap-up","Wrap-up",[17,75,76],{},"I never imagined it was an image problem — kept barking up the wrong tree, even thought my router was broken. Turns out it was a dumb mistake all along.",{"title":78,"searchDepth":79,"depth":79,"links":80},"",2,[81,82,83,84],{"id":14,"depth":79,"text":15},{"id":22,"depth":79,"text":23},{"id":36,"depth":79,"text":37},{"id":72,"depth":79,"text":73},"Nodejs","2019-04-29 20:06:34","I've been studying Node.js + Firebase lately so haven't had much time to write. But while practicing Node.js I hit a really silly problem that stuck me for three days — quick note on the fix.","md","en",{},true,"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002Fnodejs-mysterious-double-request","1",{"title":6,"description":87},false,"en\u002FNodejs\u002Fnodejs-mysterious-double-request",[98,99],"Node.js","Troubleshooting",null,"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F29\u002Fnodejs-mysterious-double-request\u002F","WraHtcsyHi9kq3nmpp7g-EuRTuAP4HfpFT8YIWjeL00",{"newer":104,"older":108},{"url":105,"title":106,"date":107},"\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2019\u002F05\u002F02\u002Fhow-much-are-you-willing-to-sacrifice\u002F","How Much Are You Willing to Sacrifice for What You Want?","2019-05-02 10:24:41",{"url":109,"title":110,"date":111},"\u002Fen\u002Flearning\u002F2019\u002F04\u002F26\u002Fmindset-adjustments-when-learning\u002F","Mindset Adjustments When Learning Something New","2019-04-26 15:35:12",[113,118,123],{"url":114,"title":115,"date":116,"readingMinutes":117},"\u002Fen\u002Fnodejs\u002F2026\u002F01\u002F13\u002Frun-multiple-commands-with-concurrently\u0